name: application of plant protection product, by airplane | application of plant protection product, by airplane | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/29968/documentation

This dataset represents the application of protection product by an agricultural airplane in one hectare (ha). The Functional Unit (FU) is one hectare and the operation time is about 0.00625 hour per ha. Plant protection product is not included. This is a service activity. 

The activity starts from the agricultural field foreseen to be processed.

This activity ends with the application of plant protection product. The inventory includes the airplane input, kerosene consumption, and emissions from the fuel. The amount of protection products is not taken into account.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/016:Support activities to agriculture and post-harvest crop activities/0161:Support activities for crop production

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: The inventory is modeled for agricultural production system in the United States.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: This activity is performed by an agricultural airplane, with a weight of 2012 kg and an operation capacity of 160ha/hour.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: The dataset is modeled for agricultural production system in US. Data Quality indicators are adjusted accordingly. Scaled for 0,877 kg of input of kasorese based on the transport, passenger aircraft, very short haul. GLO
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Average calculation based on 4 different agricultural aircrafts (Moraes, T.R., Cornago Junior, V.M., De Araújo, V.C., Esperancini, M.S. and Antuniassi, U.R., 2021. COST OF AERIAL AND GROUND SPRAYINGS AND TECHNOLOGICAL REPLACEMENT POINT: A CASE STUDY IN THE REGION OF MINEIROS, GO, BRAZIL. Engenharia Agrícola, 41, pp.359-367.) & 171.6 l/hour average consumption of kerosene, 160ha/hour based on (Moraes, T.R., Cornago Junior, V.M., De Araújo, V.C., Esperancini, M.S. and Antuniassi, U.R., 2021. COST OF AERIAL AND GROUND SPRAYINGS AND TECHNOLOGICAL REPLACEMENT POINT: A CASE STUDY IN THE REGION OF MINEIROS, GO, BRAZIL. Engenharia Agrícola, 41, pp.359-367.) and (Albaugh, T.J., Vance, E.D., Gaudreault, C., Fox, T.R., Allen, H.L., Stape, J.L. and Rubilar, R.A., 2012. Carbon emissions and sequestration from fertilization of pine in the southeastern United States. Forest Science, 58(5), pp.419-429.)."
